If you are a mergers-and-acquisitions banker for Goldman Sachs Group Inc. i=
n Russia, basically your whole business right now consists of:=09Not gettin=
g mandated for deals, because Russian businesses are more suspicious of Ame=
rican banks than they were two weeks ago.=09If you do get mandated for a de=
al, checking with compliance to make sure that the deal does not run afoul =
of any sanctions.=09Getting told by compliance =E2=80=9Cthis deal raises to=
o many sanctions risks, so we have to say no.=E2=80=9D=09Even if you do get=
 mandated and the deal gets through compliance, some internal committee or =
senior executive is going to say =E2=80=9Care we sure we want the reputatio=
nal risk of doing this deal=E2=80=9D and shut it down anyway.=09Even if the=
 deal gets approved, Russia=E2=80=99s economy is crashing so how much money=
 are you really going to make anyway?I suppose that if you are, say, a Gold=
man=C2=A0bond trader=C2=A0in Russia, the opportunities are richer, but also=
 you can probably trade those bonds somewhere else.=C2=A0And so:Goldman Sac=
hs Group Inc. said it plans to close its operations in Russia, the first ma=
jor Wall Street bank to leave in response to the nation=E2=80=99s invasion =
of Ukraine.=E2=80=9CGoldman Sachs is winding down its business in Russia in=
 compliance with regulatory and licensing requirements,=E2=80=9D the compan=
y said Thursday in an emailed statement. =E2=80=9CWe are focused on support=
ing our clients across the globe in managing or closing out pre-existing ob=
ligations in the market and ensuring the well-being of our people.=E2=80=9D=
The Wall Street powerhouse has maintained a presence in Russia in recent ye=
ars, but the country doesn=E2=80=99t amount to a meaningful portion of its =
global banking business. At the end of 2021, the firm=E2=80=99s total credi=
t exposure to Russia was $650 million, most of which was tied to non-sovere=
ign counterparties or borrowers.While Goldman is exiting Russia, the firm i=
s still trading corporate debt tied to the country without the bank itself =
making wagers on price movements.This strikes me as a fairly easy decision?=
 The upside of Goldman=C2=A0keeping a presence in Russia so its bankers can=
 go around and meet with Russian corporate clients to pitch deals seems ver=
y low. The downsides seem bad.
